<br>
Now I think there are a few reasonable and practical solutions that will solve a great deal of these problems. One warriors are the only pure melee that I'm aware of that do not have a kinda passive special abilityas they progress in lvl. For example monks get their damage table upgrade and rogues double backstab... which enhances the offensive nature of their classes with monks being more all around and rogues a bit more specialized. Now warriors do get triple attack but so do monks so that doesn't really count and with the nature of warriors being a defensive class is not really what I think they are looking for. I know someone is going to say something about defensive or evasive disciplines. Well I'm am more looking to a passive ability that doesn't require a recharge time nor has a time limit. So let's move on from that one plz. Also base hps I believe should not be counted as a defensive class ability, but rather more I gave up hps to be able to buff myself. As for a solution there is one factor that would give warriors their distinctiveness back, and I know this has been said before and I'm sure it will be said again, but I believe that this distinction should be a measureable and distinctive reduction in the damage table that warriors recieve. Much in line with how monks have their damage increased. Not an AA ability or a spell effect on some piece of equipment, but a passive ability granted to 50+ warriors purely by the fact that they are of the warrior class. <br>
<br>
Now on the exp tank envy issue I think that warriors should just maybe accept that maybe you can't have it all... that maybe the being the raid tank you need to give up a bit of appeal for the exp group. Basically as hybrids have accepted their roles maybe you should too... I don't think there is a respectable hybrid out their that expects to be the MT on boss lvl encounters.. so why should warriors expect to be kicken ultra aggro exp grinding tanks either. As warriors expect hybrids and damage dealers to manage their aggro on raids... so should warriors respect the fact that they should be able to let it fly on mobs they can actually tank. Now with slow migration on higher tier mobs I think warriors will find that their role will return. For in many ways it's SLOW that has allowed trivialized exp mob tanking more than hybrid aggro...for is it not slow the #1 reason that the instant aggro is needed in the first place which has allowed hybrids to take the spot of prefered exp tank rather than the inability of warriors to tank. With the diminishing results of slow on higher encounter mobs comes the placement of warriors role again....<br>
<br>
Which would be further reenforced with the defensive table adjustment as stated before. <br>
<br>
Ok well I've already been a bit long winded on this one... but I hope my point reasonable and somewhat logical ?<br>
<br>
