<br>
If there really needs to be something done, just nerf the Knights and get it over with.  Any solution you can come up with that involves improving warriors ends up making Knights obselete which is a lot worse than just a nerf. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=468916">Phantron</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=burzumdurbatuluuk>Burzum Durbatuluuk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/3/03 5:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2853.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: My Suggestion on Hybrid Question</span><hr size=1> Who said anything about retroactive PoP mob damage increases? I'm suggesting an ability warriors should prob. have always had... and knights don't need to be nerfed... as I already stated it's the quick aggro needed to negate the aggro from slow that makes knights cool in exp grinding... not that they tank any better or for tanking is trivial in most exp zones once mobs are slowed... been said again and again<br>
