<br>
If you improve Warriors in any way the game has to be correspondingly harder because the game is obviously tuned with Warriors as tanks in mind, otherwise the game becomes too easy.  But that makes the game too hard for everyone else.  SoE isn't going to let you make warrior Gods.  At best they'll let everyone else useless.<br>
<br>
We may have needed our mitigation table in the past but in PoP, /disc defensive reigns supreme once again.   <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=468916">Phantron</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ulvrim>ulvrim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/3/03 6:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2853.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   .</span><hr size=1> I know someone else came with this suggestion about increased mitigation for warriors also earlier in some other thread. His view (and I kindof liked the thought, thats why I'm posting it) was to give warriors innate 20% or so better mitigation than knights and remove /disc defensive from the game, or at least nerf it seriously. I don't know, I don't have a problem with knights being prefered in xp-groups on my server. I only have a problem with other warriors :P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=burzumdurbatuluuk>Burzum Durbatuluuk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/3/03 3:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2853.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: .</span><hr size=1> Ok maybe I can clarify my point a little... now ok yes defensive is still nessisary in boss lvl encounters... now I don't know the exact increase that monks have to their damage table for I doubt it's a 20% increase from monk using Jade Mace from everyone else using that weapon for example. Although I could be wrong. Basically what I was suggesting was to place a comperable damage reduction increase. Now with things quading for 2k+ or more defensive will still be nessisary in boss lvl encounters. What that innate damage reduction would provide more for is 3rd tier exp groups or groups looking to kill named mobs where the mobs hit harder and thus would return the advantage to the warrior with his or her more efficient damage migration. <br>
<br>
Just a thought... might not even be a good one <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  but just a thought on how to return a warrior's nitch and let the knights keep one. <p>&lt;center&gt;<br>
