</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=phantron>Phantron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 147<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/3/03 10:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2853.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: My Suggestion on Hybrid Question</span><hr size=1> It's really impossible to improve warriors fundamentally especially when you're dealing with mitigation because that has the effect of either making the game easier for everyone or making everyone else weaker as you retune mobs to fit this new mitigation ability warriors have.  The former basically never happens unless SoE decides they made an encounter too hard.  When you improve warriors, you basically end up nerfing everyone else because the game is balanced around warriors.  If the balance is to be kept after warriors are better, then mobs necessarily have to be more powerful.<br>
<br>
Without increasing other class's mitigation, if warrior receives any significant mitigation, then something that a warrior can tank would cream a knight, and something a knight can tank a warrior can tank trivially.  Of course, if you increase everyone's tanking ability then that's doing exactly nothing at all.<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=468916">Phantron</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=brikbludgaard>Brik Bludgaard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/4/03 1:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2853.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   the answer is nerf defensive and EB</span><hr size=1> <br>
The answer is to nerf EB and /defensive...<br>
<br>
Get warriors some better innate taunting that doesn't require EB.  (EB should help, not be the end-all-be-all.)<br>
Add in a numerical taunt adder...  like perhaps add 50hate to kick (hit or miss) OR make a new &quot;kick&quot; that adds 100hate (hit or miss) and doesnt stun or knockback... (either would use KICK/BASH timer)<br>
<br>
<br>
Reduce /defensive effectiveness and then add an INNATE damage reduction to warriors. (15%?) and a lesser one for Knights (5-7%)  While yer at it, unnerf monks...<br>
<br>
<br>
ALL of the disciplines need a rehash...<br>
<br>
I fully support defensive/aggresive/evasive becoming PERMANENT disciplines (that is until you turn them off, or use another perma discipline), with a reduction in overall effectiveness that balances their now Permanent status... (and the innate damage reduction)<br>
<br>
WAR/ROG/MNK should have two types of disciplines,  perma, and short-duration.... the two types of disciplines should be separate when it comes to reuse-timers. (perma ones have no re-use, they have disadvantages built-in)<br>
<br>
Hybrids should only have the short duration ones.<br>
(but those they have should be pretty spectacular...)<br>
one offensive and one defensive.<br>
<br>
We shall see.<br>
<br>
Brik <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hyardgune>Hyardgune</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 192<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/4/03 9:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2853.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: the answer is nerf defensive and EB</span><hr size=1> The problem isn't in mitigation.  Warriors could mitigate 300% better than knights, but that mitigation does you absolutely no good if you aren't getting hit in the first place.<br>
<br>
Warriors need some kind of better aggro generation, preferably intrinsic to the class and not another AA.  There are already too many posts with ideas for additional aggro generation.<br>
<br>
Oh, and yes, disciplines need to be completely overhauled, for every class.  Many of the warrior ones are almost valueless, even if we weren't always making sure we had defensive or evasive ready for immediate use, simply because of pathetic durations and absurdly long reuse timers.  Or they are just crap to begin with. <p>Ghune<br>
